                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Phila</placeName>\n                <date>April 11th 1867</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Mr. A. Hart</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><sic>Alow</sic> me to trouble you again for my<lb/> friend.\n                    <persName>Dr. Morris Coster</persName> in <placeName>N. Y. City</placeName>, for\n                the pur<lb/> pose to know if <persName>Dr. S. Mulder's</persName> Bible from<lb/>\n                <placeName>Amsterdam</placeName> (<placeName>Europe</placeName>) “Bybel voor de\n                Israeli<lb/>tische jeuzd” has been translated from the Dutch<lb/> into the English\n                language by certain “<hi rend=\"underline\"><persName>Peres</persName></hi>” and<lb/>\n                if <hi rend=\"underline\"><persName>Rev. Leeser</persName></hi> has been the editor?\n                That is<lb/> what my friend wrote me this morning to inquire<lb/> after.</p>\n            <p>In thanking you very much for your trouble<lb/> I hope to be forwarded with your kind\n                reply and<lb/> in the meantime I have the honor to be<lb/> most respectfully. Yours\n                obediently</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">E. Lione Dz</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>My Address is:</p>\n            <p>\n                <persName role=\"author\">Mr E. Lione Dz</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <placeName>230 South Eight Strt Phila</placeName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3fx74f3x/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
